Kung Fu Tea has bubble tea enthusiasts for its extensive menu, which includes various tea-based drinks, milk teas, fruit teas, slushes, and more. They offer a range of flavors and customizable options, allowing customers to personalize their drinks according to their preferences. Whether you enjoy classic milk tea, fruity blends, or unique specialties, Kung Fu Tea aims to provide diverse choices to satisfy different taste preferences.
Awesome place! I wish they had one in Peachtree City!

Both drinks were great. There is a small sitting area inside to hangout. Good place to try out dome new flavors of asian tea.

As for the drinks, I got a Mocha Slush with bubbles and it was delicious. 4/5 only because the drink did have some ice left that was unground, but that had no impact on the flavor or how much I enjoyed it.

Hello Kiwikappin,

Thanks for coming to our store and trying out one of our many teas an beverages that we have to offer. I understand that our Thai tea isn't what you're used to. The tapioca pearls delicious and are never hard or cold/frozen as I have found with some places so I always appreciate that.

Thank you for your critiques. We will keep them in mind and use them to create a better experience for you and others. 

KFT management.

reviews_data.review_text: My roommate & I didn’t even get a chance to order bc the barista decided to have an attitude but that’s okay Komma Tea (bubble tea shop in concord mills) isn’t too far anyways 🤷🏾‍♀️
The sign said they close at 8:30 PM. When I get there around 6ish they were closed. Like why even post up your hours if you can't stay open then? They have my lost my business.
The drinks are great but this was my second time getting milk tea spilled all over place

Best Boba tea in Charlotte!!! As a boba tea addict I do make it my mission to try all the boba spots near me. Although, I always want to try other flavors, I can’t resist and I always get the Taro it’s toooo good, I do try different toppings though and they are all delicious. The tapioca pearls delicious and are never hard or cold/frozen as I have found with some places so I always appreciate that.

They do have the option where you can choose your sugar levels if you are being health conscious.

First visit. Store was very clean. Asked cashier for recommendations and I was not disappointed. Asked for mango bubbles  but they only had grape.  Ordered large BT WOW MILK CAP WITH GRAPE POPPING BUBBLES!  Lots of boba. Sweet/salty/chewy... GREAT!!! Very interesting combo. Ladies behind counter were very nice . wait wasn't long. Will be going back. Thanks ladies!

The employees are really nice and hard working, even when having complicated orders. The inside is small and clean. Kung Fu isn't my top list of boba tea, but I do like Cocoa Cream Wow. Always get it. :)
Excellent Taro Milk tea. Definitely going back to try the other flavors.
Refreshing ☺️
Loved the teas especially the new one curvy
Good drinks and friendly staff!!

This place is honestly nasty, none of the drinks tasted good. I bought 4 drinks, Thai tea, taro milk tea, coconut milk tea and a mango tea. The Thai tea tasted like coffee, the taro tasted like butter, the coconut tasted like soap and the mango tasted vary strong. I have been going to boba tea shops for years and I was very unhappy. Wasted over 25$:(
The tea was great. I got Honey Green Tea with classic Boba and red bean paste. If they sold more snacks than popcorn i would have tried them.
Wonderful selection! Fast service and clean space. The boba is so good! I got the Chai Milk with boba and milk cap.

I have to say this used to be my spot for bubble tea but lately I have been disappointed in it. The other day I ordered a Thai tea and I don’t even think that’s what I got it tasted nothing like it and had no ice in it whatsoever. I also tried a milk tea and it just tasted like straight milk. I think it’s time to find a new bubble tea place

Apparently I've stumbled upon a very popular chain store for a very popular style of drink called, "Bubble Tea." (Yes, I'm clearly an old, sheltered Gen Xer who doesn't scroll through memes or dash from trend to trend!) But dddddddaaaang why didn't somebody tell me about this tea sooner?? Cool little nook of a shop with not a lot of room to move around but a whole bunch of choices for clever non-alcoholic energy-drenched super drinks. Never had bubbles in my tea. Girl at the front says if I don't like it, she'll replace it. She made HER favorite for me. Now it is MY favorite. Thanks, Kung Fu Tea Girl, I greatly appreciate you. You rock!
I told barista what I like from other places and she made this incredibly good drink: Ginger tea-milk and add espresso 😎 10/10

I am a frequent customer at this location. Was asked to wait outside if I didn’t have a mask (which has never happened at this location) I did so with no problem. Shortly after another customer entered with no mask and was serviced with no issue. Just be consistent, that’s all I ask.
I had chi tea milk drink. It was ok but my granddaughter had Taro slush with beads and hers was very good

It was so bad… I would give a 0 but that’s not possible… so I give you a 1 lol

you cannot customize drinks the way you want even though it says in the menu. for example, there was a picture of brown sugar tea and brown sugar milk tea was not available said by the cashier when there is clearly brown sugar syrup on the counter. is that syrup for show? LOL and was willing pay extra for brown sugar too but was not allowed to purchase anything brown sugar related which boggles my mind.
Really good tapioca pearls! I got a passion fruit black tea punch with mango jelly and boba.
I love the decor and vibe of the place. Nice staff and love the caramel milk tea. Will definitely come back.

This is the first time I went to the Kung Fu Tea and we had a great experience! I tried the Winter melon tea and it was delicious. What I liked the most is that the place was very clean and the bathrooms were very clean as well. I definitely appreciate this!
I recommend this place with 5 stars! 😃
amazing experience! i had the milk tea and it was really good. i definitely recommend this place, it’s always super clean and the staff is so nice!

I went here allot but last night was horrible the drinks were watered down after I said less ice on all orders they didn’t answer the phone last night when I called so I called in morning  and they told me it was nothing they can do due to them not answering the phone last night when I had the drinks  talking to the assistant manager and she had no customer service I WONT BE COMING Again and u should also seek now management as well

Thai Milk teas is made with white powder like substance instead of milk and tea concentrate.
I don’t recommend this place for Thai milk tea
Great customer service! Great product..along with a smile, goes along way 👍💯🔥
I'm not a big tea person but the coffee flavor was amazing. Staff was really friendly. I know, weird that a person who doesn't like tea goes to a boba tea shop. Hush
My favorite place to grab a nice bubble tea when I'm in town. Very clean and well run.
Best tea in Charlotte.
Got a matcha milk cap bubble tea, I love the anime theme of the store!  The tea itself had a good flavor to it, nice and refreshing!
Thank you for bringing in more culture to country!
Wonderful staff but my drinks barely had sweetness to them.

Great Kung Fu Tea! The drinks are 😋 delicious! One of my favorites are the sesame Matcha but all are amazing!

Clean place and great customer service!

Thank you:)
Boba was hard.
Finally a Kung Fu tea in the university area!
It's always the MATCHA with regular boba for me!!! See y'all again soon!
Great experience with the staff! So friendly and helped with questions I had to find a drink that would accommodate my being vegan. I had the white grape slush and it was delicious!
